# Defaults for `act` when run inside this repo (nektos/act, https://nektosact.com).
#
# Why --env-file=/dev/null:
#   `act` auto-loads ./.env as --env-file, which leaks dev shell vars
#   (e.g. DASS_DATABASE_URL pointing at the docker-compose `postgres` host)
#   into the runner and SHADOWS the workflow's own `env:` block. That made
#   alembic try to resolve host `postgres` from inside the act runner, even
#   though integration-ci.yml sets DASS_DATABASE_URL=...@localhost:5432/...
#   Pointing --env-file at /dev/null disables the auto-load; workflow `env:`
#   wins. Pair with .actignore (excludes .env from the cp'd workdir).
--env-file=/dev/null
